<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Note: This different from football where you can substitute a player if he is not playing well. This regarding when players have serious injuries midgame like a hamstring or a ACL tear. Doesn&#39;t this give advantage to the other team ?</p> <p>Edit : Like in international matches we can substitute a batsman with a batsman or pacer with a pacer. However the match official should approve that the injury is serious and also that the sub is like to like. </p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/NeecheSayTopper"> /u/NeecheSayTopper </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wgme11/why_cant_we_have_substitutions_for_serious/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wgme11/why_cant_we_have_substitutions_for_serious/">[comments]</a></span>